<subSubSection box="[199,1362,1479,1501]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1264,2022]" box="[199,1362,1479,1501]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,1479,1500]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a Latin word, meaning needle-like, and refers to the shape of embolus; adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1264,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1509,1532]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male of the new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1887" box="[700,782,1510,1532]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Chrysilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lauta">
<emphasis box="[700,782,1510,1532]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">C. lauta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Proszy nski &amp; Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="2010" box="[833,967,1510,1532]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Chrysilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deelemani">
<emphasis box="[833,967,1510,1532]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">C. deelemani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Proszy nski, J. &amp; Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L." pageId="0" pageNumber="65" pagination="153 - 188" refId="ref1793" refString="Proszy nski, J. &amp; Deeleman-Reinhold, C. L. (2010) Description of some Salticidae (Araneae) from the Malay Archipelago. I. Salticidae of the Lesser Sunda Islands, with comments on related species. Arthropoda Selecta, 19, 153 - 188." type="journal article" year="2010">Prószyṅski &amp; Deeleman-Reinhold 2010: 159</bibRefCitation>
, figs 30–37), but differs from the others by the wider than long RTA with a ventral tip and the much longer embolus (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 4–7" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1808,1829]" captionTargetBox="[179,1427,785,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-117@1.[151,1436,779,1801]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 4–7. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. from Chongqing. 4. Left male palp, ventral view; 5. Same, retrolateral view; 6. Epigyne, ventral view; 7. Vulva, dorsal view. CD = copulatory duct; CO = copulatory opening; Em = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD = sperm duct; SP = spermathecae." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Figs 4–5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[203,269,1571,1593]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–18" captionStartId="2.[151,257,1548,1569]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-229@2.[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8–18. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. (17 and 18 from the same specimen of Mt. Jinyun, 15 and 16 from others of Mt. Jinyun). 8. Male habitus, dorsal view; 9. Female habitus, dorsal view; 10. Posterior margin of male carapace, showing spines; 11. Male eyes and chelicerae, front view; 12. Male cheliceral teeth; 13. Left male palp, ventral view; 14. Same, retrolateral view; 15–17. Epigyne, ventral view, cleared; 18. Vulva, dorsal view, cleared." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">13–14</figureCitation>
). Female of this new species is the first known female of a true 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1887" box="[932,1026,1571,1593]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Chrysilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[932,1026,1571,1593]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Chrysilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from those of other species presently included in the genus by anteriorly located copulatory openings with the same distance as the diameter of them and the piriform spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[557,649,1632,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–7" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1808,1829]" captionTargetBox="[179,1427,785,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-117@1.[151,1436,779,1801]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 4–7. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. from Chongqing. 4. Left male palp, ventral view; 5. Same, retrolateral view; 6. Epigyne, ventral view; 7. Vulva, dorsal view. CD = copulatory duct; CO = copulatory opening; Em = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD = sperm duct; SP = spermathecae." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Figs 6–7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[659,726,1632,1654]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–18" captionStartId="2.[151,257,1548,1569]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-229@2.[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8–18. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. (17 and 18 from the same specimen of Mt. Jinyun, 15 and 16 from others of Mt. Jinyun). 8. Male habitus, dorsal view; 9. Female habitus, dorsal view; 10. Posterior margin of male carapace, showing spines; 11. Male eyes and chelicerae, front view; 12. Male cheliceral teeth; 13. Left male palp, ventral view; 14. Same, retrolateral view; 15–17. Epigyne, ventral view, cleared; 18. Vulva, dorsal view, cleared." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">15–18</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1264,2022]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,1662,1685]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Total length 6.71–9.70. 
<typeStatus box="[642,731,1663,1684]" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[747,836,1663,1684]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="1.[151,258,724,745]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,157,695]" captionTargetId="figure-114@1.[151,1436,157,695]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. from Chongqing. 1. Photo of female; 2–3. Photos of male." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Figs 2–3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[849,938,1663,1684]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–18" captionStartId="2.[151,257,1548,1569]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-229@2.[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8–18. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. (17 and 18 from the same specimen of Mt. Jinyun, 15 and 16 from others of Mt. Jinyun). 8. Male habitus, dorsal view; 9. Female habitus, dorsal view; 10. Posterior margin of male carapace, showing spines; 11. Male eyes and chelicerae, front view; 12. Male cheliceral teeth; 13. Left male palp, ventral view; 14. Same, retrolateral view; 15–17. Epigyne, ventral view, cleared; 18. Vulva, dorsal view, cleared." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">8, 10–12</figureCitation>
) total length 7.41. Prosoma 2.77 long, 2.02 wide; opisthosoma 4.60 long, 1.38 wide. Dorsum of prosoma dark brown, oval, fairly broad and longer than wide, iridescent setae locating on head region. Thorax region covering with short, dense, brown hairs. Six spines and a notch locating near the pedicel (
<figureCitation box="[158,227,1755,1777]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–18" captionStartId="2.[151,257,1548,1569]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-229@2.[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8–18. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. (17 and 18 from the same specimen of Mt. Jinyun, 15 and 16 from others of Mt. Jinyun). 8. Male habitus, dorsal view; 9. Female habitus, dorsal view; 10. Posterior margin of male carapace, showing spines; 11. Male eyes and chelicerae, front view; 12. Male cheliceral teeth; 13. Left male palp, ventral view; 14. Same, retrolateral view; 15–17. Epigyne, ventral view, cleared; 18. Vulva, dorsal view, cleared." pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Fig 10</figureCitation>
). Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.64, ALE 0.34, PME 0.09, PLE 0.35; AME–AME 0.02, AME–ALE 0.02, PME– PME 1.55, PME–PLE 0.35, ALE–PLE 0.78. MOA 0.95 long, front width 1.20, back width 1.69. Clypeus height 0.11. Chelicerae elongate, brown, with two promarginal and one retromarginal teeth. Endites and labium brown, longer than wide. Sternum orange, oval-shaped, with sparse orange hairs. Legs long and slender, yellowish brown. Femur I with black anterolateral surface and beautifully blue metal luster when live. Ventral spines locating on the surface of forelegs. Leg measurements: I 7.56 (2.27, 3.03, 1.49, 0.77); II 5.34 (1.69, 1.97, 1.26, 0.42); III 5.72 (1.68, 1.93, 1.42, 0.69); IV 6.87 (1.97, 2.37, 1.86, 0.67). Leg formula: 1432. Opisthosoma long, much narrower than prosoma. Dorsum brown, with a white longitudinal marking on the mid-line and several brick red small markings on the lateral side of white marking centrally when live.
</paragraph>
