<figureCitation box="[318,412,1966,1988]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–7" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1808,1829]" captionTargetBox="[179,1427,785,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-117@1.[151,1436,779,1801]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 4–7. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. from Chongqing. 4. Left male palp, ventral view; 5. Same, retrolateral view; 6. Epigyne, ventral view; 7. Vulva, dorsal view. CD = copulatory duct; CO = copulatory opening; Em = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD = sperm duct; SP = spermathecae." pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Figs 4–5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[425,491,1966,1988]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–18" captionStartId="2.[151,257,1548,1569]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-229@2.[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8–18. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. (17 and 18 from the same specimen of Mt. Jinyun, 15 and 16 from others of Mt. Jinyun). 8. Male habitus, dorsal view; 9. Female habitus, dorsal view; 10. Posterior margin of male carapace, showing spines; 11. Male eyes and chelicerae, front view; 12. Male cheliceral teeth; 13. Left male palp, ventral view; 14. Same, retrolateral view; 15–17. Epigyne, ventral view, cleared; 18. Vulva, dorsal view, cleared." pageId="1" pageNumber="66">13–14</figureCitation>
). RTA wider than long, with a ventral tip. Genital bulb longer than wide, with a very long embolus anteriorly, needle-like and extending forward.
</paragraph>
