<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1735,2003]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Female (
<typeStatus box="[287,378,1735,1757]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">paratype</typeStatus>
, 
<figureCitation box="[390,453,1735,1757]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="1.[151,258,724,745]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,157,695]" captionTargetId="figure-114@1.[151,1436,157,695]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. from Chongqing. 1. Photo of female; 2–3. Photos of male." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[467,480,1735,1757]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–18" captionStartId="2.[151,257,1548,1569]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-229@2.[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8–18. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. (17 and 18 from the same specimen of Mt. Jinyun, 15 and 16 from others of Mt. Jinyun). 8. Male habitus, dorsal view; 9. Female habitus, dorsal view; 10. Posterior margin of male carapace, showing spines; 11. Male eyes and chelicerae, front view; 12. Male cheliceral teeth; 13. Left male palp, ventral view; 14. Same, retrolateral view; 15–17. Epigyne, ventral view, cleared; 18. Vulva, dorsal view, cleared." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">9</figureCitation>
) somewhat smaller than male. Total length 7.16. Prosoma 2.74 long, 2.01 wide; opisthosoma 4.53 long, 1.75 wide. Eye sizes and interdistances: AME 0.59, ALE 0.32, PME 0.07, PLE 0.35; AME–AME 0.03, AME–ALE 0.01, PME–PME 1.63, PME–PLE 0.32, ALE–PLE 0.83. MOA 0.93 long, front width 1.16, back width 1.87. Clypeus height 0.12. Leg measurements: I 5.76 (1.74, 2.32, 1.06, 0.64); II 4.70 (1.49, 1.80, 0.90, 0.51); III 5.23 (1.59, 1.68, 1.27, 0.69); IV 6.60 (1.92, 2.32, 1.67, 0.69). Leg formula: 4132. Opisthosoma relatively stronger than that of male. Dorsum brown, with three white and two brick red markings when live.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1735,2003]" pageId="2" pageNumber="67">
Epigyne (
<figureCitation box="[297,389,1919,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–7" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1808,1829]" captionTargetBox="[179,1427,785,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-117@1.[151,1436,779,1801]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 4–7. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. from Chongqing. 4. Left male palp, ventral view; 5. Same, retrolateral view; 6. Epigyne, ventral view; 7. Vulva, dorsal view. CD = copulatory duct; CO = copulatory opening; Em = embolus; FD = fertilization duct; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; SD = sperm duct; SP = spermathecae." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">Figs 6–7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[400,467,1919,1941]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–18" captionStartId="2.[151,257,1548,1569]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-229@2.[151,1436,155,1526]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 8–18. Chrysilla acerosa sp. nov. (17 and 18 from the same specimen of Mt. Jinyun, 15 and 16 from others of Mt. Jinyun). 8. Male habitus, dorsal view; 9. Female habitus, dorsal view; 10. Posterior margin of male carapace, showing spines; 11. Male eyes and chelicerae, front view; 12. Male cheliceral teeth; 13. Left male palp, ventral view; 14. Same, retrolateral view; 15–17. Epigyne, ventral view, cleared; 18. Vulva, dorsal view, cleared." pageId="2" pageNumber="67">15–18</figureCitation>
). Copulatory openings anteriorly located, separated by the diameter of the opening. Copulatory ducts extending backward. Spermathecae piriform, connecting with fertilization ducts anteriorly.
</paragraph>
